post_text:
Good evening Parents and Guardians,
This is Mrs. Gaines, Superintendent.
Although there are no confirmed cases of CoronaVirus in Kern County, we will be closing schools on Thursday, March 19 and starting our spring break a day early. Schools will remain closed through April 14. On Wednesday of this week all students in grades k - 8 will be given a packet of work that they are to complete during the weeks of March 30 through April 14. High school students will be able to complete their assigned work on their laptops. They should not be doing work during spring break. We will also be providing breakfast and lunch and also some child supervision during March 30 through April 14 for those parents that request it. Additional messages from me will be provided to keep you updated on services we will be providing after our spring break ends. Again, schools will remain open Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday of this week closing Thursday for Spring Break.
Thank you

Seniors and Parents/Guardians of Seniors:

Please join us Tuesday, November 12th from 5-7 p.m. in the library for our FAFSA/CA Dream Act completion night. Representatives from Cash for College will be here to help you fill out the FAFSA/CA Dream Act application and answer your financial aid questions. Spanish translation will be available.

It is very important that students submit a FAFSA or CA Dream Act application prior to March 2nd, even if they are not yet completely sure of their educational plans. This will ensure that students are considered for the maximum amount of aid for which they qualify.

Please reply to this email or call 661-256-5020 x325 to RSVP so we can get a head count of how many to expect. If you have any questions, please contact your student's counselor.

Hello Rosamond Families and Friends!
Help Yearbook Raise Money by Test Driving a Car!
When: Saturday, Sept. 21st 9am-4pm (mark it on your calendar)
Where: Antelope Valley Ford Dealership, 1155 Auto Mall Dr.
How do I help?
For every person that is 18 years of age and has a valid driver’s license, takes a free no obligation test drive at the AV Ford dealership, and fills out a quick survey afterwards, the RHS Yearbook club will receive $20.

• You can preregister and make sure that your time is used efficiently at the event by going to https://d4ur.com/#/pre/8KBRY.
• You can also just show up on the date, and register at the event if you would rather.

We need as many people to come and support us as possible, so if you can please share this information with your friends, siblings, parents, neighbors, on social media, with random people you meet while walking your dog, or anyone else you can think of, we would appreciate it!

If you have any questions please email
Mr. Hansen at ashansen@skusd.k12.

Hello RHS parents, guardians, and community members. Would you like to drive a Ford Mustang for free while also raising money for the RHS Yearbook club? On Saturday, September 21st, the RHS yearbook will be having a fundraiser at the Antelope Valley Ford Dealership in Lancaster. For every person to take a free no-obligation test drive of a new car that day and fill out a quick survey, the yearbook club will receive $20. You must be 18 years old and have a valid drivers license to participate. No other fundraiser gives you the option to drive a Ford mustang for free and earn 20 dollars for your school's yearbook club. We need as many people as possible to come out and support the yearbook staff on September, 21st. So please tell everyone you know about our event! Thank you for your time, and we hope to see you at AV Ford on September 21st !!

Dewine Moore- ASB President

For our RES and WES students/parents/guardians

Dear Parents/Guardians,

We wanted to send a reminder that Back to School Night is August 22, 2019. Please take this opportunity to come and meet your child’s teacher. Each teacher will be making a presentation regarding his/her classroom procedures. Come and find out what will be expected of your child this year. Communication between home and school is critical to your child’s academic success.

Upon arriving for Back to School Night proceed directly to your child’s classroom. Presentations will begin promptly at the following times:

TK/ Kindergarten/First Grade: 5:00PM-5:30PM
2nd and 3rd Grade: 5:45PM-6:15PM
4th and 5th Grade: 6:30PM-7:00PM

Thursday, August 22nd is also a minimum day with dismissal at 12:10PM at WES and 12:40 at RES.

We look forward to seeing you at Back to School Night!

post_text: TMS will be offering a new elective this year called California Cadet Corps. This new program is very similar to the ROTC program and teaches and promotes leadership, team work, citizenship, academic success, responsibility, health, wellness, and fitness. This new elective can also satisfy your student's PE requirement, which would allow students to take another elective. So, students in a mandatory elective, like Math Support, could take Cadet Corps as their PE class. If you are interested in having your student placed in the California Cadet Corps please contact the office or email me at nadams@skusd.k12.ca.us. Hurry before space runs out. For more information about the Cadet Corps you can visit the website at https://cacadets.org/

Monday-October 29

Thursday–Nov. 1
